hn Steenhuisen wins DA interim leader position |url=https://citizen.co.za/news/south-africa/breaking-news/2205737/john-steenhuisen-wins-da-interim-leader-position/ |accessdate=17 November 2019 |newspaper=The Citizen |date=17 November 2019}}</ref>\n==Personal life==\nMbombo was married and has two daughters. Her husband died in 2003.<ref name=\"spotlight\" />\n\nIn March 2020, Mbombo came into contact with the French consul-general [[Laurent Amar]] who tested positive for [[COVID-19]].<ref>{{cite news |last1=Shange |first1=Naledi |title=Western Cape health MEC self-isolating after French consul general tests positive |url=https://www.timeslive.co.za/news/south-africa/2020-03-18-western-cape-health-mec-self-isolating-after-french-consul-general-tests-positive/ |accessdate=20 March 2020 |newspaper=TimesLIVE |date=18 March 2020}}</ref> She subsequently went into [[self-isolation]] and later tested negative.<ref>{{cite news |title=Western Cape Health MEC Nomafrench Mbombo tests negative for Covid-19 |url=https://www.iol.co.za/capeargus/news/western-cape-health-mec-nomafrench-mbombo-tests-negative-for-covid-19-45234989 |accessdate=20 March 2020 |agency=IOL |date=19 March 2020}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n{{s-start}}\n{{s-ppo}}\n{{s-bef|before=[[Denise Robinson]]}}\n{{s-ttl|title=Federal Leader of the Democratic Alliance Women's Network|years=2018\u2013present}}\n{{s-inc}}\n|-\n{{s-off}}\n{{s-bef|before=[[Theuns Botha]]}}\n{{s-ttl|title=Western Cape Provincial Minister of Health|years=2015\u2013present}}\n{{s-inc}}\n|-\n{{s-bef|before=[[Ivan Meyer]]}}\n{{s-ttl|title=Western Cape Provincial Minister of Cultural Affairs and Sport|years=2014\u20132015}}\n{{s-aft|after=[[Theuns Botha]]}}\n{{s-end}}\n{{Democratic Alliance (South Africa)}}\n{{Winde provincial cabinet}}\n{{Zille provincial cabinet}}\n{{Members of the Western Cape Provincial Parliament}}\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Mbombo, Nomafrench}}\n[[Category: Living people]]\n[[Category: Democratic Alliance (South Africa) poli